The paper deals with the development and validation of a deep learning algorithm for medical image analysis, specifically for the detection of diabetic retinopathy in retinal fundus photographs. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning methods and the challenges of reproducing their results, which are relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The study involves the assessment of image gradability, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper uses publicly available data sets, which may involve information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
